This repository is meant to store reproducable experimental setups for:

Title:    Modeling Rigid Contact at the Acceleration Level: Viable and Fast
Authors:  Sam Zapolsky, Evan Drumwright

INSTALLATION:
  This package requires: 
    Moby (simulator):         github.com/edrumwri/Moby 
                              checkout version: 2c1b58619480d679e0790f247688279dbf5c00df

    Ravelin (Linear Algebra): github.com/edrumwri/Ravelin 
                              checkout version: 1674e5ea39aa22d996a81a9721cac9a2656891c2

  Additional Requirements:
    Open Scene Graph (Visualization): http://www.openscenegraph.org/
      To visualize, run all examples with the additional option: -r, else remove this option

RUNNING Experiments:
  Single point contact
    single_point_test

  Rolling down slope with small hills (diverging paths)
    Velocity Level:
      moby-driver -r -s=0.001 -p=libsimplePlugin.so ball_on_hill.xml
    Acceleration Level (sustained contact) [this work]
      moby-driver -r -s=0.00101 -p=libsimplePlugin.so ball_on_hill.xml
  
  Spinning box
    Velocity Level:
      moby-driver -r -s=0.001 spinning-box.xml
    Acceleration Level (sustained contact) [this work]
      moby-driver -r -s=0.00101 spinning-box.xml
  
  Robot Walk
    git clone github.com/PositronicsLab/Pacer
    version: 9eca375ad36ff4630890fc60c4b80f8ccc64d3dc
    Velocity Level:
      moby-driver -r -s=0.001 -p=libLinksPlugin.so links1.xml
    Acceleration Level (sustained contact) [this work]
      moby-driver -r -s=0.00101 -p=libLinksPlugin.so links1.xml
